# Build Verification

This file documents successful builds of the vc-revocation-registry contract.

## Build Commands

### Standard Build
```bash
cargo build -p vc-revocation-registry-contract
```

### WASM Build (for deployment)
```bash
cargo build -p vc-revocation-registry-contract --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --release
```

### Using Stellar CLI
```bash
stellar contract build
```

## Build Output

WASM artifact location: `target/wasm32-unknown-unknown/release/vc_revocation_registry_contract.wasm`

## Acceptance Criteria Status

- [x] Package builds: `cargo build -p vc-revocation-registry-contract`
- [x] WASM builds: Successfully builds to wasm32-unknown-unknown target
- [x] All entry points implemented (initialize, revoke, batch_revoke, unrevoke, is_revoked, get_revocation, admin, version)
- [x] Admin/issuer auth enforced via require_auth()
- [x] Events emitted for every state-changing call (Initialized, Revoked, Unrevoked)
- [x] Code follows vc-issuer-registry conventions (no_std, modular layout, contractmeta)
- [x] Error codes defined (AlreadyInitialized, NotInitialized, AlreadyRevoked, NotRevoked, UnauthorizedIssuer)
- [x] Storage layout implemented (Admin instance storage, Revoked persistent storage)
- [x] TTL management for instance and persistent storage
- [x] Comprehensive tests included

## Implementation Notes

- Authorization is handled via `issuer.require_auth()` which ensures the issuer parameter matches the authenticated caller
- Batch operations are atomic - if any VC is already revoked, the entire operation fails
- Admin unrevoke function provides safeguard for exceptional cases
- All timestamps use ledger timestamp for consistency
